                    <abstract>Maria van Antwerpen, at around 26 years old, was fired in the middle of winter in 1745. In January of the following year, she dressed as a man and enlisted in the army as sixteen year old Jan van Ant. Approximately a year and a half later Jan married Johanna Cramers, an officer's daughter. They continued to travel with the army until eventually Jan was stationed near Breda. There he was recognised by the daughter of a family for whom Maria had worked as a maid. She was arrested and sentenced in May 1751 and exiled from Brabant and Limburg and all garrison cities.</abstract>
